  "texts": [
    "Within the variants of the InterrogateLLM method, we observe that the use of an ensemble in the backward process exhibits sizeable strides across the board, suggesting that model diversity can compensate for individual model weaknesses (see also Sec.7).",
    "We conduct an ablation study to examine the impact of the multiple K backward processes performed in InterrogateLLM (Alg.1 line 4), the effectiveness of the variable temperature values (Eq.",
    "(8)), and the importance of the average function in Eq.5.",
    "Variable K values The performance of Interro-gateLLM with various values of K is evaluated on the Movies, Books, and GCI datasets, and the results are reported in Tab. 3, and Tab.",
    "9, 10 from the supplementary, respectively."
  ]
}